35. The Oblique March (see figure 7). Being at a halt or marching, the command is: 1. <hi rend="underline">Right (Left) Oblique</hi>, 2. <hi rend="underline">MARCH</hi>. Each man faces half right (left) in marching at the command of execution, and steps off in the new direction. The ranks remain parallel to the original front and the files remain at right angles to the ranks.

36. At the command <hi rend="underline">HALT</hi>, given as the left foot strikes the ground in halting from Right Oblique, or as the right foot strikes the ground in halting from Left Oblique, advance and please plant the right (left) foot in the direction of the oblique, turn to the original front on the ball of the right (left) foot, and place the other foot alongside. Thus, on halting, the unit is faced to the original front.

