55. <hi rend="underline">Correct Alignment</hi> (inset m) is assumed from <hi rend="underline">Port baton</hi> by lowering ferrule to left, allowing the staff to fall into raised left hand, and holding baton in a horizontal position at height of shoulders with both hands, thumbs to rear. The drum major faces the band was giving the signal. One short whistle blast commands the correction. The same position is used when marking time or at half step.

